; Pinned fragment exercising CDDL range and inequality constraints.
;
; Upstream source: IntersectMBO/cardano-ledger
;   path: eras/conway/impl/cddl/data/conway.cddl
;   revision: 9ae77d611ad86ae58add04b6042ab730272f2327
;
; Recorded in node/src/upstream_pins.rs.  This fragment is intentionally
; minimal — it covers only the range/inequality control operators that the
; yggdrasil cddl-codegen parser supports (`.size N..M`, `.le`, `.ge`, `.lt`,
; `.gt`).  Standalone CDDL value-ranges like `1 .. 9223372036854775807` and
; signed bounds are deliberately out of scope; they require RFC 8610 syntax
; the workspace does not yet need.
;
; The literal values below are aligned with the constructs Conway uses:
;   - `anchor_url = text .size 0..128` mirrors upstream `url` size bound.
;   - `bounded_bytes` mirrors variable-size hash slots.
;   - `.le`/`.ge`/`.lt`/`.gt` mirror per-protocol-parameter inequality
;     guards used by Conway governance ratification rules.

; --- Range size constraints (.size N..M) ---
anchor_url = text .size 0..128
bounded_bytes = bytes .size 0..64

; --- Inequality constraints (.le, .ge, .lt, .gt) ---
bounded_value = uint .le 65535
min_value = uint .ge 1
strict_lt = uint .lt 100
strict_gt = uint .gt 0

; --- Regression: existing .size N fast-path must remain bit-identical ---
fixed_hash = bytes .size 32
fixed_uint = uint .size 8
